y</span><hr size=1> I'm curious if someone could offer me some insight into how the delay of primary and offhand weapons work, and work together.<br>
<br>
I've heard a few rumors that primary handed weapon delay affects the offhand's delay.  Is this true?<br>
<br>
If it is, there's no sense in me putting a low delay weapon in my off hand, I should just find the highest damage weapon I can regardless of delay that I can use and offhand it.<br>
<br>
If it's not true, then I'm probably just fine with what I have.<br>
<br>
-Desbarolis -- 52nd bard <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon2.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uraiid.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Raiid</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Troll Assassin™</span><br>  Posts: 237<br> <font color=#E9D756>(7/10/01 11:47:00 am)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Primary/offhand dly</span><hr size=1> Each hand operates independently from the other. You want the best ratio offhand since there is no damage bonus.<br>
<br>
So for you, not having double attack..<br>
<br>
primary hand swings, dual wield skill is checked, if you succeed you swing, if not you don't. Once your OFFHAND delay has cycled another DW check is made, if you succeed you swing, of not you don't... rinse and repeat forever begin... <p>Raiid Daedsgubllik (60)<BR>
United Independent<BR>
EMarr</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/ulaoke.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Laoke</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 697<br> <font color=#E9D756>(7/10/01 4:56:30 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Primary/offhand dly</span><hr size=1>   What Raaid said is correct, and eaily verified.  Put a Lightstone in your primary hand, and attack something.  If the off-hands delay was governed by your primary hand, you'd never attack with either hand.  <br>
<br>
