erynlor <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon2.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uraiid.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Raiid</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Troll Assassin™</span><br>  Posts: 243<br> <font color=#E9D756>(7/11/01 7:28:49 am)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Primary/offhand dly</span><hr size=1> There is a damage bonus applied to each hit on weapons used in the -primary- hand, and 2 handers. This free, unresistable damage is added to EVERY succesful hit using the primary hand. <br>
<br>
The bonus goes up as you go up in level as well. The effect of this is such that at higher levels, low delay weapons will FAR outdamage higher delay weapons with the same ratio when used in the primary hand. <br>
<br>
This is best illustrated by comparing 2 weapons.<br>
the 1st<br>
a 13/20 1 hander from Sleepers Tomb, one of the hardest zones in the game. In the hands of a level 60 warrior using RBG haste this will put out 1094 damage per minute in the primary hand. Damn nice huh...<br>
<br>
The 2nd weapon 3/10 1 hander, this used to drop from a mid 30's mob in Frontier Mountains. Seems a pretty crappy ratio huh.. But when put into the hands of a level 60 warrior using an RBG, this weapon will put out... 1170 damage per minute!<br>
<br>
This is because the lower delay allows that free damage bonus to be applied more often, thus allowing it to overcome the ratio difference.<br>
<br>
For 2 handers the same principle applies.<br>
<br>
Since this bonus is not applied offhand, all you really look for is ratio.<br>
<br>
 <p>Raiid Daedsgubllik (60)<BR>
United Independent<BR>
EMarr</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uzel45.showPublicProfile?language=EN>zel45</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 39<br> <font color=#E9D756>(7/11/01 7:30:52 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Primary/offhand dly</span><hr size=1> The primary hand has a level dependent damage bonus. You start getting it around 35 if i remember correctly. It adds 1 to your damage, and gets better from there.<br>
<br>
That's why low delay wepaons are preferred in the primary hand (besides taunting) the more you hit, the more often the damage bonus gets applied. This is why VI had to nerf the moss covered twig into an offhand weapon, it had low dmg (3 or something), but it was so damn fast that, at higher levels, it did alot of damage.<br>
<br>
The secondary hand doesn't get this damage bonus, so that's why you want the best ratio you can get for that weapon. <p>Silverflower<BR>
